    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-07T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-07T01:00:00-05:00" n="993"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d993">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.014/12–745: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Robertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-07T13:00:00+07:00"
                            >December 7, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 1:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2115. In accordance with instructions last paragraph your 1776, November 1, we
                    delayed approaching Chinese authorities pending arrival and discussion with
                    General Wedemeyer in Chungking. War Dept request was conveyed to Foreign Office
                    in note Nov. 15 to which we have had no reply (re your 1915, November 29). Have
                    again requested Vice Foreign Minister<note n="2" xml:id="d993fn2">Liu
                        Chieh.</note> to expedite.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
